wiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ZergRush" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ZergRush">Zerg Rush</a>, and manage to succeed at the end of episode 7. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Turns out it was Miharu, who wanted Akihisa out of the way so she could pursue her one-sided romance towards Minami.</span> They then walk into the bath as a bonus reward, only to find out <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> that the only person taking a bath was the elderly school principal, who suspends the entire male student body for a week</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EpicFail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EpicFail">Epic Fail</a>:<ul><li> Most of the things that Akihisa thinks of. His attempts at clearing misunderstandings only exacerbate the situation more often than not.</li><li> End of Episode 2. A massive <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BatmanGambit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BatmanGambit">Batman Gambit</a> many years in the making finally pays off, allowing 2-F to beat 2-A by having Shouko get only a 97 on an elementary level test, everyone is celebrating... <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">and then Yuuji got a 53</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EskimosArentReal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EskimosArentReal">Eskimos Aren't Real</a>: Class F wonder if Shouko is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MistakenForGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MistakenForGay">attracted to Mizuki (when she's actually after Yuuji)</a>, which Akihisa dismisses that as something that only happens in fiction (it's implied he's specifically talking about porn). Minami begs to differ, whereupon we are introduced to her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PsychoLesbian" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PsychoLesbian">Psycho 